{"about_the_game":"<h2 class=\"bb_tag\"> <h2 class=\"bb_tag\"> <strong> What can Vtuber Animator do? </strong></h2></h2>Vtuber Animator is a VRM model animation player that can synchronize animations in real-time to live streaming software via the OSC protocol.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\"><h2 class=\"bb_tag\"><strong>Featured</strong></h2></h2><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li>Support *.vrm model</li></ul><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li>Support *.vmd and mixamo fbx animations</li></ul><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li>Support *.vpd poses</li></ul><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li>Animations can be switched using hotkeys</li></ul><h2 class=\"bb_tag\"> <h2 class=\"bb_tag\"> <strong> How to use? </strong></h2></h2>In <strong>Vtuber Animator</strong>:<br>Press &quot;Model+&quot; then select your model through the file picker<br>Enter ip and a port and press &quot;Connect&quot;<br>Press &quot;Import&quot; in &quot;Motion List&quot;,then select your motion through the file picker<br>Press &quot;Play&quot; button<br><br>In <strong>VSeeFace</strong>:<br>Enable the &quot;OSC/VMC Receiver (Disable Tracking)&quot; option in VSeeFace, and input the same port as entered in Vtuber Animator. <br>Optionally toggle &quot;Apply VSeeFace Tracking&quot; and any other toggles underneath it if you only want to perform partial poses.","background":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2810100/page_bg_generated_v6b.jpg?t=1708097216","background_raw":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2810100/page_bg_generated.jpg?t=1708097216","capsule_image":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2810100/capsule_231x87.jpg?t=1708097216","capsule_imagev5":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2810100/capsule_184x69.jpg?t=1708097216","content_descriptors":{"ids":[],"notes":null},"detailed_description":"<h2 class=\"bb_tag\"> <h2 class=\"bb_tag\"> <strong> What can Vtuber Animator do? </strong></h2></h2>Vtuber Animator is a VRM model 